

✅ This categorization makes it easier to **map your prep to role expectations**:  
- **Frontend Engineer** → Angular/React, UI/UX, performance, testing.  
- **Full-stack Engineer** → Add backend APIs, security, microservices.  
- **DevOps/Data Engineer** → CI/CD, cloud, big data, MLOps.  
- **Tech Lead/Architect** → System design, design patterns, leadership, communication. 


## 🟢 Frontend Development (Angular, React, UI/UX)
- **Angular Concepts**: Zone.js, AOT compilation, Interceptors, Template-driven forms, Services, Dependency Injection, Lifecycle hooks, Change detection (Default vs OnPush), ViewChild & Content Projection, Custom Directives, Pipes, HTTP calls, Lazy loading, Angular folder structure.  
- **React Concepts**: Stateful vs Stateless components, Forms/events, Popular libraries, Design patterns (MVC, MVP, MVVM).  
- **Performance & Build Tools**: Webpack, ESBuild, Gulp, Tree shaking, Performance tuning, Memory leakage handling.  
- **UI/UX & Styling**: Material design, CSS preprocessors, BEM methodology, Accessibility standards, User interface qualities.  
- **Testing & Quality**: Jasmine/Karma, ESLint, Husky, Sonar/Checkmarx, Linting (ES6).  

---

## 🔵 Backend & API Development
- **Node.js / Express.js**: REST API development, CORS handling, JWT/OAuth security.  
- **Databases**: MySQL, MongoDB, SQL fundamentals.  
- **Security**: Authentication & Authorization, OWASP knowledge, API security measures.  
- **Microservices**: Design, deployment, communication patterns.  

---

## 🟣 DevOps & Deployment
- **CI/CD**: Jenkins, AWS CodePipeline, Git, Version control, Frequent commits with proper messages.  
- **Containers & Orchestration**: Docker, Kubernetes.  
- **Deployment**: Normal builds, Docker images, Migration strategies.  
- **Monitoring & Debugging**: Sonar, Checkmarx, DevTools, Console usage.  

---

## 🟡 Cloud & Data Engineering
- **Cloud Platforms**: AWS services, Azure Synapse, Google BigQuery.  
- **Data Tools**: Databricks, PySpark, Apache Spark, Hadoop, AWS Redshift.  
- **Visualization**: Power BI, Tableau.  
- **MLOps**: Model deployment, monitoring, integration with cloud.  

---

## 🔴 Software Engineering Fundamentals
- **Design Patterns**: Singleton, Factory, Observer.  
- **System Design**: Load balancing, Caching, Sharding, CAP theorem, Consistency.  
- **Low-Level Design**: Class diagrams, OOP principles.  
- **Coding Standards**: Clean, scalable, documented codebases; code reviews.  
- **DSA Prep**: Arrays, Linked lists, Trees, Graphs, Heaps, Hashing, Sorting, Searching, Dynamic programming, Backtracking.  
- **Competitive Programming**: LeetCode practice, algorithmic problem solving.  

---

## ⚖️ Soft Skills & Leadership
- Communication & stakeholder management.  
- Leading cross-functional teams.  
- Collaboration across teams.  
- Ensuring delivery quality.  
- Mentoring developers on best practices.  

